Schottland's independent schools continue to be distinguished by academic excellence. This continued in 2018 with further outstanding examination results and is only supported by individual and joint successes in the fields of sport, art, music and other community enterprises.
With more than 30,000 students from all over Scotland, these schools represented by the Scottish Council of Independent Schools (SCIS) strive to maintain their students and their parents at the highest possible level.
Independent schools pursue the goal of preparing their students for training and higher education, the profession of their choice and their place as world citizens.
As a educational sector that can design a tailor-made curriculum and actually implement it, we see that modern languages are still popular and desired as choices in schools.
Nelson Mandela said: “If you speak to someone in a language he understands, you will reach his head.
