Children who speak several languages, especially languages of developing countries, will have better opportunities to find a useful job.
In Scotland, different languages are taught in all schools.
A number of schools will focus on the more classical modern languages, while other languages will be taught, which are considered to be the most important for the United Kingdom in 2020, for example, mandarin or Japanese.
Wherever your child's interests lie, independent schools will always have a number of languages with specialist teachers.
Scottish independent schools are committed to creating a learning environment that prepares the children and provides them with the skills necessary for their success, whatever the future looks like.
At this time, in a global economic environment, it cannot be denied that languages are still of fundamental importance for the future of the country, which is why this must be reflected in education.
